@Header(id=4) public static class Tcp.SACK_PERMITTED extends Tcp.TcpOption
The TCP SACK permitted option may be sent in a SYN by a TCP that has been extended to receive the SACK option once the connection has opened. It MUST NOT be sent on non-SYN segments.

This option has no fields. Its presence determines if TCP SACK is permitted.

Author:
Mark Bednarczyk, Sly Technologies, Inc.
